namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.

transcript.text: Welcome to on Print Shop.
In this video we will learn about how to set up header and footer links.
Let's talk about key features and benefits.
It helps you to add various links to your website.
You can add links to your websites menu such as header, footer, top, header and sidebar.
You can also apply filters based on stores and create links accordingly.
So first of all, let's have a look onto the storefront.
So as you can see this is the.
Top header section where you can see the links like track order, shopping cart, request code and login logo, registration button and shopping cart.
So this is at the top of the section.
Then we have header section in which you can see the logo of the website and all the links like home, product and category links.
And then we have the sidebar section where you can set the sidebar links in this section.
And then we have the footer where you can set the footer links.
Let's have a look into the admin.
First of all we need to go to store personalization.
Click on links header photo.
Here you can see there is a drop down to select your store in which you want to set up the link.
If you want to set up a link on the website, storefront or retail website you have to choose default store.
If you want to set up a link on the private store, you have to choose a store name from the list given.
After that you have to click on add button.
Here you can create a new link on your store.
So you have to choose the position first of all out of the given options like header, footer, top header or sidebar.
Then you have to set up a link title such as sample.
And then you can select link option whether you want to show both text and icon.
And then you have to set up the link which you want to set up on this title.
So here we have various options where you can choose content page, static page, category, group or any of these drop down options.
So I'm taking external link.
So here you can set up any external link as well such as any of your website which you want to show as a external link on your store.

So I'm taking one sample external link and here you have option to choose whether you want to allow your customer to access the link before or after login on your website or you can choose both and then you have to select option to open the link in a new window or in the same window.
Then you have to set up the sorting order and then keep the status active to show up on your your website and then save it.
Now when we go to the storefront and when we refresh the page here we can see there is a link created called sample and here is the page it's showing.
So in this way, you can create links on your website.
Thank you for watching this video.
In case of any further concern, feel free to connect with us.
Have a nice day.
